cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper describes a proof assistant based on a type theory and focuses on the construction and manipulation of derivable judgments. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses a meta-level programming language used to build derivable judgments. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of a proof assistant and its components. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely categories as they are not directly related to the content of the paper.
